  "summary": "Windows HDR auto close",
  "environment_raw": null,
  "description": "When I start the game, the HDR function of the Windows system well automatically turned off. n n n n",
  "Steps to Reproduce": "1. Ensure that HDR is enabled in the Windows display settings before starting the game.\n2. Launch Minecraft from the Windows 10 launcher.\n3. Observe the game's loading process until you reach the main menu.\n4. Check the Windows display settings to confirm if the HDR functionality is still enabled after the game has started.\n5. Exit the game and recheck the Windows display settings to see if HDR remains disabled.",
  "Environment": "Minecraft Java Edition Version 25w32a (snapshot)",
  "Observed Behavior": "When launching Minecraft on a Windows system with HDR (High Dynamic Range) enabled, the HDR functionality is automatically disabled upon game startup. This occurs regardless of the current HDR settings in Windows. The user experiences a noticeable change in visual quality, as the game reverts to standard dynamic range, impacting the overall brightness and color depth of the graphics. \n\n- **Steps to Reproduce:**\n  1. Ensure HDR is enabled in the Windows display settings.\n  2. Launch Minecraft.\n  3. Observe that HDR is automatically turned off after the game starts.\n\n- **Expected Behavior:**\n  The game should maintain the HDR setting as configured in the Windows system, allowing for enhanced visual fidelity during gameplay.\n\n- **Environment:**\n  - Windows version: [insert specific version]\n  - Minecraft version: [insert specific version]\n  - Monitor: [insert monitor model with HDR support]\n  - Graphics settings: HDR enabled in Windows settings prior to launching the game.\n\nThis issue needs to be addressed to ensure that players can enjoy the intended visual enhancements that HDR provides while playing Minecraft.",
  "Expected Behavior": "When launching Minecraft on a Windows system with HDR enabled, the HDR functionality should remain active throughout the game session. The game should not interfere with the Windows HDR settings, allowing players to experience enhanced visuals as intended. If HDR is enabled in Windows settings prior to starting the game, it should automatically be detected and maintained during gameplay, ensuring that the graphical fidelity and color range are optimized for the player's display. Users should not encounter any automatic disabling of HDR when starting the game, and the game should run smoothly with HDR effects applied as per the system settings.",
